<h2>Why are habits important?
</h2>

<p>Habits are the bread and butter of our daily lives, since they make up the majority of our subconscious actions and how we live. So if we want feel better and improve our lives, one of the best places to start is by getting better habits.
</p>

<p>If our habits don’t help us, they are unhealthy or make us feel bad, then that can have a negative affect our lives. Meanwhile if our habits are built up to benefit us, then we can live a healthier lifestyle much more easily.
</p>

<p>Switching up our bad habits for good ones doesn’t just improve our quality of life, by helping us feel better in ourselves, but it can help others feel better too (just imagine how fun we are to be around when we’re hangry).
</p>

<p>Habits, like getting good quality sleep, have a large range of health benefits such as reducing our chance of getting colds, and improving our metabolism and self-control. Morning routines can help us to feel calm and energised, and allow us to more easily achieve our goals. Meanwhile physical activity reduces our risk of cardiometabolic diseases like heart disease and diabetes.
</p>

