<h2>Our first habits
</h2>

<p>Since our habits are built up when we repeatedly respond in the same way to a prompt, a lot of our habits would have been built in our childhoods.
</p>

<p>If you grew up having dinner at 8pm, then you’re more likely to have dinner at 8pm when you’re an adult. The same goes for the time we go to bed and the time we wake up. As well as other daily tasks, like whether we eat breakfast or skip it, when or if we brush our teeth and how frequently we shower or tidy.
</p>

<p>However, our habits can change either by circumstance or by deliberate choice. When I had early starts for work, it became a habit to get up at 6am (or even earlier) and have a long walk. When I was doing my masters project, I would have a morning run at 8am. But when I was writing up my thesis, I would often sleep in til 2pm in the afternoon, and exercise became a hopeful-dream.
</p>

